It took him 28 minutes to bring the receipt after taking the credit cards to process the payment. He walked past the table holding it in his hand and servicing the tables right next to us. —After bringing it we were shocked that we didn’t have any copies of our receipt and looked to mobile banking to see the pending charges. They were uneven amounts meaning the waiter added gratuity onto the each check with no permission or signature. After confronting him and asking where the receipt was and how could he just add on gratuity without any permission he panicked and said it was an accident. Everyone understands very well that any server will come and thank you at the end of service to provide a receipt and knowing that they would be tipped based on the service which they provided. The point is check your receipts! Unacceptable! I do not recommend to anyone.

It was my girlfriends and I first time in the Dupont Circle area of DC. We really wanted a good place to eat with reasonable prices, so we went to Daily Grill on a whim. I'm so glad we did! We went during their happy hour and I must admit, it was one of the best happy hours I've ever been to! They had fantastic martinis for only $6 and their apps were no more than $5. All together, for a party of 8, our bill came to $125! And we each had at least 3 cocktails each plus an array of apps. Our server, I want to say her name was Amy (she had long red hair) was amazing! Very attentive and courteous. She even treated me to a complimentary dessert for my birthday. Going to Daily Grill was one of the highlights of my trip to DC. I highly recommend you go here, you won't be disappointed. One of my friends arrived late with her husband, when I recommended Daily Grill to her and she tried it, she loved it as well! Great job Daily Grill, keep up the fantastic work!

(Translated by Google) It is a nice place, classic American restaurant with classic style with wooden walls and warm. With a touch of modernity in its bar and open kitchen. The food is rich, the Wednesday special is highly recommended. It is a pork loin with rib, prepared in a blackberry sauce and free accompaniment for an extra, the baked potato is highly recommended, the portion is quite abundant and even to share. The Pot Pie is his signature dish and it is highly recommended the puff pastry used is not so greasy and it has been served very hot. In essence it is the cream of your choice (chicken, lobster and meat) covered in puff pastry. It is also a sufficient portion for a person. Your lemonade is made with natural lemon juice and is quite nice. Its bread is handmade and has a neutral flavor that goes well with its warm butter.  (Original) Es un lugar agradable, clásico restaurante americano con estilo clásico con paredes de madera y cálido. Con un toque de modernidad en su barra y cocina abierta. La comida es rica, el especial de los miércoles es muy recomendable. Es un lomo de cerdo con costilla, preparado en una salsa de zarzamora y acompañamiento libre por un extra, la papa horneada es muy recomendable, la porción es bastante abundante e incluso para compartir. El Pot Pie es su platillo insignia y es bastante recomendable el hojaldre utilizado no es tan grasoso y viene servido muy caliente. En escencia es la crema a tu elección (pollo, langosta y carne) cubierta de masa hojaldre. También es una porción suficiente para una persona. Su limonada está elaborada con jugo de limón electra natural y es bastante agradable. Su pan es artesanal y tiene un sabor neutro que va bien con su mantequilla templada.
